104694.name: Prevalence of overweight adults (males) - WHO (2019)
104694.description: Prevalence of overweight males aged 18 and above. A person is defined as overweight if they have a body-mass index (BMI) equal to or greater than 25. BMI is a person's weight in kilograms divided by his or her height in metres squared.

display.name: Share of men that are overweight

source.name: Prevalence of Overweight Adults - WHO (2019)
source.dataPublishedBy: World Health Organization (WHO), Global Health Observatory
source.additionalInfo:
This dataset presents estimates of the prevalence of overweight men and women aged 18 and above by country, region, and globally.

A person is defined as overweight if they have a body-mass index (BMI) equal to or greater than 25. BMI is a person's weight in kilograms divided by his or her height in metres squared.

Estimates are based on data from a random sample of the general population.
